Police say arrests have yet to be made after two teenage boys were wounded in apparent gang shootings in Belhar. CAPE TOWN - Police say arrests have yet to be made after two teenage boys were wounded in apparent gang shootings in Belhar.A 12-year-old boy was shot in the shoulder and his 14-year-old friend was wounded in the leg.The shooting took place at a park in Extension 13, earlier this week.The police's Frederick van Wyk says: It s been reported that a Toyota Tazz stopped at a corner and occupants started shooting at the two victims. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)